ARM Holdings, Anglo American, BP: U.K., Irish Equity Preview

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-26T00:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/arm-holdings-anglo-american-bp-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
that may have unusual share-price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  The FTSE 100 Index fell 9.76 points, or 0.2 percent, to
5,925.26. The FTSE All-Share Index dropped 0.2 percent to
3,082.80, while Ireland’s ISEQ Index retreated 0.4 percent to
2,914.96.  Anglo American Plc (AAL)  : The mining company said
thermal coal production in  South Africa  stopped “completely”
after workers started a strike over pay on July 22. The stock
gained 0.1 percent to 3,026.5 pence.  ARM Holdings Plc (ARM)  : The owner of chip technology
used in Apple Inc. iPhones is due to report first-half earnings.
The shares advanced 1 percent to 616 pence.  BG Group Plc (BG/)  : The U.K.’s third-largest natural gas
producer is scheduled to report first-half earnings. The stock
gained 1.1 percent to 1,425 pence.  BP Plc (BP/)  : The London-based oil producer is using
“coercive tactics” to force victims of the 2010 Gulf of Mexico
oil spill to agree to final settlements with a claims fund,
lawyers suing the company said. The stock gained 1.1 percent to
475.40 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  